frameDefinitions: This frame consists of LUs which denote a Theme ceasing motion.
A Guest stays for a time at a Location, which is not his or her permanent residence, for some Duration.
An Agent causes Air to move in a direction, usually specifying either in or out of the body.
A man-made artifact, digital or physical, which is used to display information presented via the object.
Generally without overall (translational) motion,  an Agent places a Theme at a location, the Goal, which is profiled.
frameExamples: Peter <t>stopped</t> immediately and span to see Aeryn frozen where she stood.
I usually <t>stay</t> with my aunt at her summer house when I go to Seville.
4chan is an <t>image</t> <t>board</t> for discussing gaming and internet culture.
David <t>placed</t> his briefcase on the floor.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies <fen>Theme</fen> whose motion ceases.

This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Theme</fen>'s motion stops.
The <fen>Guest</fen> remains for a relatively short period of time in the <fen>Location</fen>.

The length of time that the <fen>Guest</fen> remains at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Host</fen> is living at the <fen>Location</fen> on a permanent basis, and is allowing the <fen>Guest</fen> to stay there.
The time at which the temporary stay takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates the larger physical setting of the temporary stay.
The <fen>Agent</fen>'s breathing causes the motion of the <fen>Air</fen>.  <fen>Agent</fen> is generally the External Argument.
<fen>Air</fen> is the substance that the <fen>Agent</fen> causes to move.
The time at which breathing occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the breathing occurs.
This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes location during the Placing.
The role <fen>Goal</fen> is the location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up. This role is profiled by words in this frame.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Placing occurs.
